  "uuid": "7642d3ba91d29caf9e21e3fba2dd3dbb",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quality Manager (Shipyard)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Establish and maintain the <strong>Quality Management System (QMS)</strong> to define procedures, documentation, and standards required to ensure consistent quality across all shipbuilding and repair operations.</p></li><li><p>Ensure all projects comply with high-quality standards, customer specifications, and mandatory regulatory requirements from classification societies and relevant authorities.</p></li><li><p>Lead the <strong>Quality Control team</strong> to inspect and verify each stage of vessel construction, with particular focus on critical areas such as welding, fabrication, and coating, ensuring strict adherence to engineering specifications and technical drawings.</p></li><li><p>Ensure vessels meet all safety and structural standards set by classification societies and international maritime regulations, coordinate audits, and manage the resolution of any quality issues.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Minimum 5 years of relevant shipyard experience.</p></li><li><p>Bachelor’s degree or Diploma in Naval Architecture, Marine Engineering, or a related field.</p></li><li><p>Proficient in AutoCAD and general computer applications.</p></li><li><p>Solid understanding of shipbuilding processes and ability to interpret technical specifications and engage with trades and clients.</p></li><li><p>Strong analytical, communication, and interpersonal skills.</p></li><li><p>Willingness to work permanently at a shipyard in Batam. </p></li></ul>",
